                    <h3>Composite particles</h3>
                    We can combine fundamental particles in order to form composite particles. which satisfies the following ``logic'' table, for positive intenger $n$:<br><br>
                    $(n)-$Bosons  &#8611;   Composite  Boson <br>
                    $(2n)-$Fermions  &#8611;   Composite  Boson <br>
                    $(2n+1)-$Fermions  &#8611;   Composite  Fermion <br>
                    <br>
                    Examples include the proton (1/2), the neutron (1/2), Bose-Einstein (1). Several composite particles, have powerful (potential) technological applications. 
                    <br><br><br>

<br><br>		     
